Create a new promptcode preset based on a description.

When asked to create a preset, run:
```bash
promptcode preset create <preset-name>
```

This will:
1. Create a new preset file in `.promptcode/presets/`
2. Add the specified file patterns
3. Make it available for use with other commands

After creation, edit `.promptcode/presets/<preset-name>.patterns` to refine the file patterns.

Example: `promptcode preset create authentication-system`